Now, they have little sections of Huawei, like furniture and other things that we could do. But when you cut out sections, it gets very complicated: whats being sold, whats coming in. So, at this moment, it looks much more like were not going to do business. I dont want to do business at all, because it is a national security threat.
And I really believe that the media has covered it a little bit differently than that. So were looking, really, not to do business with Huawei. And were actually talking about not doing any business, because, again, the rest of it is not national security, but its very difficult to determine whats coming in and whats not coming in. Its still Huawei.
So well be making a decision over that in the not-too-distant future. But its a little bit the opposite of what seemed to be reported this morning.
