I remember, growing up, we had mental institutions. Then they were closed -- in New York, Im talking about. They were -- many of them were closed. A lot of them were closed. And all of those people were put out on the streets. And I said -- even as a young guy, I said, "How does that work? Thats not a good thing." And its not a good thing.
